comments.body:
The {{hadoop-yarn-server-timelineservice {color:#333333}include is because the policy generator test spins up an RM to make sure that parsing the queue structure from the RM web service endpoint is working, and the timeline service is an injected dependency in the RM web service.{color}}}

I've fixed the other concerns and submitted a new patch.

Thanks for reviewing [~giovanni.fumarola]!

Thanks [~youchen] for the patch, few comments:

*{{DefaultGlobalPolicy}}*
 * It should be called {{NoOpGlobalPolicy}} or something similar.

*PolicyGenerator*
 * {{invokeRMWebService}} can return null. Please add NullPointer checks in {{getSchedulerInfo}} and {{getInfos.}}
 * Line 193. Change the conf.get into 
{code:java}
conf.get(YarnConfiguration.GPG_POLICY_GENERATOR_BLACKLIST);
{code}
 and add a NullPointer check after. It makes cleaner.

*TestGPGPolicyFacade*
* Add javadoc for the tests.

In general keep the word {{SubCluster}} in this way around the patch.

